The paper discusses a method for improving the training time of a transformation-based learner, which is a common technique used in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance of the modified learner compared to other systems, which suggests that it may fall under categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as NLP is often used in this field.
